). Gnathosoma . Hypostomal setae ( bs ) bifurcate; oral setae ( or ) simple and smooth. Supracoxal setae of palps absent. Palp trochanter ( 20–25 long) without setae, palp femur ( 47–62 ) and genu ( 17–20 ) each with 1 barbed seta. Palp tibia ( 37–42 ) with 3 barbed setae and distally bifid odontus, 13–16 long. Palp tarsus ( 67–74 ) considerably exceeding tibia, with single solenidion ω, 4 setulose and 3 barbed setae. Palpal setal formula (fPp) = 0-B-B-BBB 2-7 Bω. Cheliceral base 42–47 long, cheliceral blade curved and with 2 distinct subterminal teeth, 17–25 long (
